IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO IMPROVE THE LIVES OF THE MOST VULNERABLE PEOPLE IN THE COMMUNITIES THAT WE SERVE THROUGH IMPROVED HEALTH STATUS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO IMPROVE THE LIVES FOR ALL PEOPLE IN THE COMMUNITIES WE SERVE THROUGH IMPROVED HEALTH REGARDLESS OF THE ABILITY TO PAY FOR THE SERVICES.
IRS990.Desc: TO IMPROVE THE LIVES OF THE MOST VULNERABLE PEOPLE IN THE COMMUNITIES THAT WE SERVE THROUGH IMPROVED HEALTH STATUS. WE STRIVE TO DO THIS BY PROVIDING ACCESS TO PRIMARY AND PREVENTATIVE MEDICAL, DENTAL, AND MENTAL HEALTH SERVICES, APPROPRIATE HEALTH EDUCATION AND SUPPORTIVE CASE MANAGEMENT WITHOUT REGARD TO ABILITY TO PAY FOR SERVICES OFFERED. WE PROVIDE PATIENTS ACCESS TO SERVICES EQUALLY, WITHOUT REGARD TO RACE, COLOR, RELIGION, OR NATIONAL ORIGIN.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: PUBLIC CHARITY CLASSIFICATION ------------------------------- STERLING HEALTH SOLUTIONS, INC.'S PUBLIC CHARITY CLASSIFICATION HAS BEEN DESIGNATED AS A HOSPITAL DESCRIBED IN SECTION 180(B)(1)(A)(III) BY THE IRS. SCHEDULE H HAS NOT BEEN COMPLETED BY STERLING HEALTH SOLUTIONS AS IT DOES NOT OPERATE A STATE LICENSED HOSPITAL FACILITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: INCOME TAXES -------------- THE ORGANIZATION'S AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS DID NOT INCLUDE A FOOTNOTE THAT ADDRESSED THE ORGANIZATION'S LIABILITY FOR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS UNDER FIN 48 (ASC 740). MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THEIR INCOME TAX POSITIONS UNDER THE GUIDANCE INCLUDED IN ASC 740. BASED ON THEIR REVIEW, MANAGEMENT HAS NOT IDENTIFIED ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS TO BE RECORDED OR DISCLOSED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PROCESS TO REVIEW FORM 990 --------------------------- A DRAFT OF THE FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO BOARD MEMBERS TO BE REVIEWED PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ---------------------------- DISCLOSURE AND ATTESTATION IS REQUIRED TO MONITOR AND ENFORCE COMPLIANCE WITH THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. IF DISCUSSION AND/OR VOTE ARE BEING TAKEN ON AN ISSUE REPRESENTING A CONFLICT OF INTEREST OR AN APPARENT CONFLICT OF INTEREST FOR A MEMBER, THE BOARD MEMBER SHALL EXCUSE HIMSELF/HERSELF FROM THE VOTE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION REVIEW --------------------- THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND HUMAN RESOURCES DEPARTMENT CONDUCT AN ANNUAL COMPENSATION REVIEW OF THE CEO BY REVIEWING THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS SALARY AND BENEFITS REPORT, THE GROWTH AND ACCOMPLISHMENTS OF STERLING HEALTH SOLUTIONS, AND BY COMPARING SIMILAR NONPROFIT HEALTHCARE ORGANIZATIONS' REVENUES AND COMPENSATION DATA AVAILABLE ON GUIDESTAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION REVIEW ---------------------- THE CEO AND HUMAN RESOURCES DEPARTMENT CONDUCT AN ANNUAL COMPENSATION REVIEW OF KEY EMPLOYEES AND OFFICERS OF THE ORGANIZATION USING COMPARABILITY DATA.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AVAILABILITY OF DOCUMENTS -------------------------- THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST AT THE DISCRETION OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND MANAGEMENT.
PART-YEAR OFFICERS --------------------- RICK GRANT WAS THE CFO OF STERLING HEALTH SOLUTIONS UNTIL DECEMBER 31, 2021. FLORENCE MAHONEY BECAME CFO EFFECTIVE JANUARY 1, 2022.
